  "text": "The Firefox Servo CSS style system integration consists of the following core components in the layout/style directory:\n\n1. **ServoStyleSet** (layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h/cpp) - The main entry point for style resolution. This class manages the set of style sheets that apply to a document and is backed by a Servo Stylist. It contains methods for rule changes, style invalidation, and document state changes.\n\n2. **ServoBindings.h** - The Gecko-to-Servo FFI (Foreign Function Interface) declarations. This header defines C FFI functions that allow Gecko code to call into Servo's style engine. Key functions include Servo_CssRules_GetStyleRuleAt, Servo_StyleSet_StyleRuleChanged, and numerous other Servo_* functions for CSS rules and style operations.\n\n3. **RestyleManager** (layout/style/RestyleManager.h/cpp) - The component responsible for scheduling and managing style recalculation. It includes the RestyleManager class (which tracks restyle operations and manages the restyle generation counter) and ServoRestyleState (a stack class for passing restyle state through the traversal).\n\n4. **ServoUtils.h** - Utility functions for Servo traversal state. This header provides critical utilities like IsInServoTraversal() (checks if code is executing during a Servo traversal), InitializeServo(), ShutdownServo(), and AssertIsMainThreadOrServoFontMetricsLocked(). It also exposes the external variable sInServoTraversal for efficient thread state tracking.\n\n5. **moz.build** - The build configuration file for layout/style that lists all source files, headers, and build targets for the CSS style system.\n\nThe resolution pipeline flows as follows: ServoStyleSet is the main orchestrator that manages which styles apply to elements. When style changes occur, RestyleManager is invoked to schedule recalculations. ServoBindings provides the FFI layer that allows C++ code to call into the Rust-based Servo style engine. ServoUtils provides utility functions and thread-state tracking to ensure safe operation during the traversal phase."
}

